@@YACK!MUD TNG — Rules@@N

There are three rules.  They cover everything.

@@R#1  Don't be a dick.@@N

  This applies to players, to staff, and to the game itself.  Griefing,
  harassment, deliberate abuse of mechanics to ruin someone else's
  experience — all of it falls here.  Use your judgment.  If you have to
  ask whether something counts, it probably does.

@@R#2  If you make an immortal take action, everyone involved loses.@@N

  When a dispute or violation requires staff intervention, the response
  will not be surgical.  Everyone involved — instigator, participants,
  bystanders who made it worse — can expect denial, IPban, or deletion.
  No warnings, no appeals, no reimbursements.

  Do not waste the immortals' time.  Do not drag others into situations
  that will cost them their characters.

@@R#3  Multiplaying is allowed.  Automation is not.@@N

  You may run up to @@c3 characters simultaneously@@N.  Play them however
  you like, including having them interact with each other.

  @@eFully automated, scripted, unattended play is prohibited.@@N  A
  trigger that fires a spell or command in response to a prompt is fine.
  A bot that plays the game for you while you are away is not.
  Automated play discovered by staff will be treated as a Rule #2
  violation — meaning everyone on the account and any associated
  accounts should expect consequences.

@@b---------------------------------------------------------------------@@N

  That is the entire ruleset.  It is intentionally short because the
  goal is a game people want to play, not a legal document.

  See also:  @@cHELP NEWBIE@@N   @@cHELP IMM@@N
